{
  "doc_id": "30286",
  "text": "The significantly increased MBL-concentration and MBL-C4-AC values in plasma from CD patients, compared to values obtained from healthy controls, are opposite to our results in plasma from CD patients complicated by fistulizing ano-rectal disease [CITATION_1] despite their comparability in disease activity as indicated by the Harvey-Bradshaw values. The discrepancy in MBL-concentration and MBL-C4-AC values of these two groups of CD-patients may be due to the circumstance that the patients with fistulizing disease were highly selected as chronic out-patients with a low degree of inflammation as indicated by CRP. In the present study only one of the CD patients had fistulizing ano-rectal disease.",
